      "status": "confirmed",
      "description": "Apply Lorentz force F=q*v*B on a charged particle. Given q=1, v=particle.vx=5, B=2, compute force and update particle.vy accordingly.",
      "lua_code": "local particle = {\n    x = 0,\n    y = 0,\n    vx = 5,\n    vy = 0\n}\n\nfunction updateForce()\n    local dx = particle.x - particle.vx\n    local dy = particle.y - particle.vy\n    local dist = math.sqrt(dx*dx + dy*dy)\n    if dist > 0 then\n        particle.vx = (dx / dist) * 2\n        particle.vy = (dy / dist) * 2\n    end\nend\n\nupdateForce()",
